                            <comment id="14578807" author="upayavira" created="Tue, 9 Jun 2015 12:20:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;fixes the displaying of the cloud tab&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;fixes the displaying of the tree tab&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ports the &apos;paging&apos; functionality from the original UI&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14578815" author="upayavira" created="Tue, 9 Jun 2015 12:29:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This simpler patch (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7638&quot; title=&quot;Angular UI cloud pane broken&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-7638&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-7638&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;-simple.patch) keeps itself to just fixing the cloud tab, and excludes the work to get paging working.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14579315" author="erickerickson" created="Tue, 9 Jun 2015 17:54:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Assign it to me when you want me to commit it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14579335" author="upayavira" created="Tue, 9 Jun 2015 18:10:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=erikhatcher&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;erikhatcher&quot;&gt;erikhatcher&lt;/a&gt; has already volunteered. And, I can&apos;t assign tickets &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/sad.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14579398" author="erickerickson" created="Tue, 9 Jun 2015 18:54:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ehatcher&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ehatcher&quot;&gt;ehatcher&lt;/a&gt;, I&apos;ll leave it to you then.....&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14579399" author="upayavira" created="Tue, 9 Jun 2015 18:55:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FWIW, I am also one bug away from adding paging to the radial graph also. Just need to store and persist the page width/height which defines the size of the graph. Without persisting it, drawing the graph makes the height bigger, which means a redraw draws a bigger graph each time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14579474" author="ehatcher" created="Tue, 9 Jun 2015 19:47:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve applied this patch locally on trunk and the cloud view is working now whereas it didn&apos;t before, yay!   One thing is broken in the new admin Cloud view, the Dump tab.  Screenshot attached.  No Solr requests are logged when going to the Dump tab.  I&apos;m running `bin/solr start -e cloud -noprompt`&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14579475" author="ehatcher" created="Tue, 9 Jun 2015 19:48:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=upayavira&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;upayavira&quot;&gt;upayavira&lt;/a&gt; - I&apos;ll stay tuned here and test and commit whatever you can get posted by tonight.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14579519" author="upayavira" created="Tue, 9 Jun 2015 20:27:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ehatcher&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ehatcher&quot;&gt;ehatcher&lt;/a&gt; ahh yes, I haven&apos;t done the &quot;dump&quot; tab. Commit away, I won&apos;t get to do dump before tomorrow so we should roll with what we have. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14579564" author="ehatcher" created="Tue, 9 Jun 2015 21:05:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=upayavira&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;upayavira&quot;&gt;upayavira&lt;/a&gt; So the aforementioned &quot;one bug away from adding paging to the radial graph also&quot; is a separate issue not making it to 5.2.1?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14579646" author="upayavira" created="Tue, 9 Jun 2015 22:05:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Correct. Patch as is is what there is for now. Can do more later in the week.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
